<TITLE> 47 die in boat capsize </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Kishoregonj, Dec 4 (bdnews24.com)At least 47 people drowned and scores were missing on Friday after a boat capsized on the Daira river in Mithamoin upazila. Kishoregonj deputy commissioner Mohammad Shah Alam told bdnews24.com the accident took place at around 9:30am when a Bhairab-bound engine boat collided with passenger ferry MV Al-Helal near Charigram in Mithamoin upazila. Divers re-floated the engine boat and found three more bodies, raising the death toll to 47 from initially reported 44 dead. Jasimuddin, a survivor of the accident, said the boat was carrying around 100 passengers to Karimganj from Kadamchhal village of Ashtogram upazila. Alam said divers and local people recovered 47 bodies. The victims have not yet been identified. This was the second ferry accident in a week. Some 85 people died on Nov 27, the night before Eid-ul-Azha, when MV Coco-4, partially capsized at Nazirpur river station in Lalmohan, some 40 km from Bhola district town. The vessel, crowded from hull to decks with people heading home to celebrate the holiday with families, began tipping with the weight of disembarking passengers and partially sank. bdnews2
